---
// The Challenge section for Property Management industry page
---

<section id="challenge" class="cre-challenge-section">
  <div class="cre-challenge-container">
    <span class="section-label">THE CHALLENGE</span>
    <h2 class="cre-challenge-headline">
      Speed vs. process in property management
    </h2>
    <p class="cre-challenge-subheadline">
      Property management requires constant coordination across multiple properties, tenants, vendors, and systems. Most property management companies are still running on spreadsheets, fragmented communication, and reactive maintenance that burns out teams and frustrates tenants.
    </p>

    <!-- Highlight Box -->
    <div class="cre-highlight-box">
      <p class="cre-highlight-text">
        "The average property management firm spends 40-50% of staff time on administrative tasks instead of tenant relationships."
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Challenge List -->
    <div class="cre-challenge-list-wrapper">
      <ul class="cre-challenge-list">
        <li><strong>Tenant communication is fragmented</strong> across email, phone calls, and multiple platforms—making it impossible to track requests and ensure nothing falls through the cracks.</li>
        <li><strong>Maintenance scheduling is reactive</strong> instead of preventive. Maintenance teams coordinate through email and notes, leading to emergency repairs that cost more and damage tenant relationships.</li>
        <li><strong>Financial management requires manual reconciliation</strong> of rent payments, expenses, and vendor invoices across properties, delaying insights into profitability.</li>
        <li><strong>Tenant onboarding is time-intensive</strong>, requiring manual document collection, lease setup, and communication—slowing down move-ins and creating errors.</li>
        <li><strong>Rent collection is inconsistent</strong>, with no automated reminders or late-payment follow-up, leading to higher collection periods and cash flow delays.</li>
        <li><strong>Property performance is opaque</strong> because reporting requires manual data pulls across systems, making it hard to identify underperforming units or optimize pricing.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Stat Cards -->
    <div class="cre-stat-cards">
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">40-50%</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">administrative overhead</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">5-7 days</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">tenant onboarding</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cre-stat-card">
        <div class="cre-stat-number">15-20%</div>
        <div class="cre-stat-label">late rent payments</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .cre-challenge-section {
    background: #FFFFFF;
    padding: clamp(30px, 4vw, 50px) 24px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-container {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .section-label {
    display: block;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 2px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #000000;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-headline {
    font-family: 'Figtree', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', sans-serif;
    font-size: clamp(40px, 5vw, 56px);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: #000000;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-subheadline {
    font-size: 16px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    max-width: 900px;
  }

  .cre-highlight-box {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border-left: 4px solid #0EA5E9;
    padding: 32px;
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .cre-highlight-text {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: #000000;
    font-style: italic;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list-wrapper {
    margin-bottom: 64px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 32px;
    font-size: 17px; /* Increased from 16px for better readability */
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li::before {
    content: '−';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: #0EA5E9;
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .cre-challenge-list li strong {
    font-size: 17px; /* Match parent font size */
    color: #000000;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .cre-stat-cards {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
  }

  .cre-stat-card {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.2);
    padding: 32px;
    text-align: center;
    transition: all 0.4s ease;
  }

  .cre-stat-card:hover {
    background: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.1);
    border-color: rgba(14, 165, 233, 0.4);
  }

  .cre-stat-number {
    font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px);
    font-weight: 400;
    color: #0EA5E9;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .cre-stat-label {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.7);
    text-transform: lowercase;
  }

  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .cre-challenge-list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li {
      font-size: 16px; /* Slightly smaller on tablet */
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li strong {
      font-size: 16px; /* Match tablet size */
    }

    .cre-stat-cards {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .cre-challenge-section {
      padding: clamp(20px, 3vw, 40px) 24px;
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li {
      font-size: 15px; /* Original size on mobile for space efficiency */
    }

    .cre-challenge-list li strong {
      font-size: 15px; /* Match mobile size */
    }

    .cre-highlight-box {
      padding: 24px;
    }

    .cre-stat-card {
      padding: 24px;
    }
  }
</style>

